100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 4, 1925, the world witnessed significant developments as the League of Nations convened in Geneva to address ongoing tensions in Europe, notably concerning reparations from Germany. In the United States, the trial of John T. Scopes continued, igniting a national debate over evolution and education. Meanwhile, the British Empire faced political strife as the Labour Party struggled to maintain unity amidst economic challenges.
